  m_text: "Ph\u1EDF is one of the most famous Vietnamese noodle soups and is often
    eaten for breakfast or lunch. The dish is believed to have originated in Northern
    Vietnam before spreading across the country. It consists of rice noodles served
    in broth with beef or chicken and fresh herbs. Main ingredients include broth
    bones, rice noodles, green onions, cilantro, and spices such as cinnamon and
    star anise. \r\n"
